#Introducing Lists

Lists are a collection of objects

Can be created with the syntax: list_maker = ['bob', 3]

The index of a list starts at 0, so list_maker[0]
corresponds to 'bob'

Index can be negative to count from end, i.e.
-1 is last value, -2 is second from last, etc

Reassign values in a list with variable assignment

list_maker[0] = 'steve'

## List Methods

.append() - add a value to the end of the list

.insert(index, value) - insert a value into a
specific index 

del list_maker[index] - delete an item from a
specific index

.pop(index) - take the last item and return it, 
or specify an index to pop

.remove(value) - remove an item based on it's
value. Only removes the first occurrence

.sort(reverse=True) - sort a list permanently in alphabetical
order, or reversed

sorted(list, reverse=True) - returns a 
temporarily sorted list, can be reversed

.reverse() - reverse the order of the list

len(list) - returns the length of the list




